# Pre-Deploy Checklist — Quality Gate for AI Agents

You are a senior full-stack engineer doing a final pass before this code ships to production.
Go through every section below in order. Check it, fix it if broken, mark it PASS or FAIL.
Do not skip sections. At the end, output the summary table. If any row is FAIL — do not deploy.

---

## 0 — IDENTIFY YOUR STACK

Note which apply: Next.js / Nuxt / SvelteKit | Supabase / PlanetScale / Firebase | Supabase Auth / Clerk / Auth0 | Stripe / Paystack / M-Pesa / Razorpay / Paddle | Upstash / Cloudflare rate limiting | Sentry / Datadog

---

## 1 — BUILD INTEGRITY

```bash
npx tsc --noEmit
npx eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx --max-warnings 0
npm run build
```

- [ ] Zero TypeScript errors
- [ ] Zero ESLint warnings or errors
- [ ] Production build completes without crashing
- [ ] No `@ts-ignore` or untyped `any` without a comment
- [ ] No `console.log` in production code
- [ ] No blocking TODO or FIXME comments

---

## 2 — ENVIRONMENT & SECRETS

- [ ] All `.env` files are in `.gitignore`
- [ ] No secret keys inside any `NEXT_PUBLIC_` or client-exposed variable
- [ ] No database admin/service role keys in client components
- [ ] Payment provider secret keys are server-side only — only public keys go to the client
- [ ] All required env vars documented in `.env.example`
- [ ] All env vars set in deployment dashboard (Vercel / Railway / Render / etc.)
- [ ] Run `git log --all --full-history -- "*.env"` — no secrets in git history

---

## 3 — AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION

- [ ] Every API route checks for valid session before executing logic
- [ ] Server Actions validate session server-side — not just client guards
- [ ] Role checks (admin, paid user, etc.) enforced server-side — not just hidden in UI
- [ ] Protected pages redirect unauthenticated users
- [ ] Tokens never stored in `localStorage` — use `httpOnly` cookies
- [ ] Auth redirect URLs validated against an allowlist — no open redirects

---

## 4 — DATABASE SAFETY

- [ ] Row-level security (or equivalent) enabled on every table with user data
- [ ] Tested: can User A read/write User B's rows? (must fail)
- [ ] Admin credentials only used in server-side admin operations
- [ ] No DELETE or UPDATE without a WHERE clause scoped to the authenticated user
- [ ] Migrations up to date — no schema drift between local and production
- [ ] Sensitive columns not returned in wildcard SELECT * queries to the client

---

## 5 — INPUT VALIDATION & SANITIZATION

- [ ] All API request bodies validated with a schema (Zod / Yup / Joi) on the server
- [ ] File uploads: MIME type validated, size capped, never executed
- [ ] User-generated HTML content sanitized (DOMPurify / sanitize-html) before render
- [ ] URL params used in DB queries are validated — no raw string interpolation
- [ ] Phone numbers validated for correct format before passing to SMS/payment provider

---

## 6 — ERROR HANDLING

- [ ] Every async API route wrapped in try/catch
- [ ] Errors return correct HTTP status codes (400 / 401 / 403 / 404 / 500) — not always 200
- [ ] Error responses: `{ error: string }` shape — no raw stack traces to client
- [ ] Every fetch/axios call on the client has error handling with user feedback
- [ ] Loading, error, and empty states handled for every data-fetching component
- [ ] React Error Boundaries around high-risk sections (video, payments, real-time)

```typescript
// Required pattern for fetch inside useEffect
useEffect(() => {
  const controller = new AbortController();
  fetchData({ signal: controller.signal }).catch((err) => {
    if (err.name === 'AbortError') return;
    setError(err.message);
  });
  return () => controller.abort();
}, [dependency]);
```

---

## 7 — RATE LIMITING

- [ ] Auth endpoints rate limited — max attempts per IP per minute
- [ ] OTP / verification code endpoints rate limited — max 5 per 15 minutes
- [ ] AI / LLM endpoints rate limited per user
- [ ] Payment trigger endpoints rate limited per user — prevent duplicate charges
- [ ] Webhook endpoints validate provider signature before processing
- [ ] Rate limit responses return HTTP 429 with Retry-After header

---

## 8 — PAYMENT SAFETY (applies to all providers)

- [ ] Webhook signature verified using provider header before fulfilling any order
- [ ] Payment verified server-side via provider API — never trust client success callbacks
- [ ] Duplicate webhook deliveries handled — idempotency check before acting
- [ ] Subscription plan IDs stored server-side — client cannot self-assign a paid plan
- [ ] Test mode credentials never active in production — controlled by env var

**Stripe:** use `stripe.webhooks.constructEvent()` | verify on `payment_intent.succeeded`
**Paystack:** verify `x-paystack-signature` HMAC SHA-512 | call `/transaction/verify/:reference`
**M-Pesa / Daraja:** HTTPS callback only | validate payload structure | confirm via query API
**Paddle / Razorpay / others:** same pattern — verify signature → confirm server-side → idempotency

---

## 9 — SECURITY HEADERS & CORS

- [ ] CORS explicitly configured — no wildcard `*` on authenticated APIs
- [ ] Allowed origins list only known, trusted domains
- [ ] Content Security Policy header set
- [ ] `X-Frame-Options: DENY` to prevent clickjacking
- [ ] HTTPS enforced — no mixed content
- [ ] Cookies: `Secure`, `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Strict` or `Lax`

---

## 10 — REAL-TIME & SUBSCRIPTION CLEANUP

- [ ] Every subscription has a cleanup/unsubscribe in useEffect return
- [ ] Video/audio calls disconnect on component unmount — not only on button click
- [ ] Chat clients disconnect on logout
- [ ] WebSocket connections closed on unmount

---

## 11 — PERFORMANCE

- [ ] Images optimized with explicit dimensions — no layout shift
- [ ] Large lists paginated or virtualized
- [ ] AI/LLM calls use streaming where possible
- [ ] No useEffect running on every render due to wrong dependency array
- [ ] Heavy libraries (3D, charts) lazy-loaded

---

## 12 — NOTIFICATIONS & BACKGROUND JOBS

- [ ] Failed notifications don't crash the app
- [ ] Cron jobs have error handling and alerting on failure
- [ ] Email sends are non-blocking — a failed email doesn't fail the user's action
- [ ] Background jobs are idempotent — safe to run twice

---

## 13 — LOGGING

- [ ] Error tracking (Sentry / Datadog / etc.) capturing unhandled errors in production
- [ ] Critical events (payments, auth) logged with context — never PII or card data

---

## 14 — DEPLOY READINESS

- [ ] Tested on mobile viewport (375px minimum)
- [ ] New public routes added to sitemap
- [ ] Database migrations ready to run in production
- [ ] Rollback plan defined
- [ ] Correct branch confirmed — no stale experimental branches

